    {
      "event": {
        "id": "vdt7vdm56wmk7chit8",
        "project_id": "t2n81sremiemji271r4",
        "created_at": "2026-01-09T20:44:52.988Z",
        "local_audio_uri": "file:///var/mobile/Containers/Data/Application/171121ED-FC13-410A-8985-271D6F0AC7D8/Documents/audio/recording_1767991487887_2lqdooee2k5mk7chevj.m4a",
        "transcript_text": "On level one, we realized even after building flush that there was negative or positive pressure throughout the building due to the airflow coming in from the south side of the building, which meant that some of the bathroom doors, especially the ones with the showers, are not closing when left to close by themselves. So this needs to be fixed and also needs to be considered on next projects. And door frame and hardware needs to be made aware that this condition could occur again.",
